Firſt, The Apoſtle in himſelf gives us a Deſcription of a living Chriſtian in theſe words, For to me to live is Chriſt; or as Tremellius (from the Syriac) and others render it, Vita enim mea Chriſtus eſt. For Chriſt is my Life, underſtanding that the Apoſtle uſeth the Infinitive
〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉 . to live, for the Noun
〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉 . Life; which is very uſual both in Scripture and other Authors: and being thus underſtood, the words contain this Propoſition;
